calDirWorkspace: no isolation,\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:4:GitBranchWorkspace is THE ROLLBACK MECHANISM (roadmap 2.7): every attempt runs\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:22:LocalDirWorkspace is the \"go straight to the repo dir\" output strategy: no\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:39:from src.domain.value_objects.lifecycle import FailureKind\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:74:class GitBranchWorkspace:\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:195:                f\"workspace begin failed: {exc.stderr}\", FailureKind.TOOL_ERROR\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:224:                FailureKind.TOOL_ERROR,\nbackend/src/infra/git/workspace.py:296:class LocalDirWorkspace:\nbackend/src/infra/container.py:143:        FailureKind taxonomy as the real CLI runners) or real (per-task\nbackend/src/app/runtime_failures.py:14:from src.domain.value_objects.lifecycle import FailureKind\nbackend/src/app/runtime_failures.py:44:    kind: FailureKind\nbackend/src/app/testing/fakes.py:21:from src.domain.value_objects.lifecycle import FailureKind\nbackend/src/app/testing/fakes.py:260:class NoOpWorkspace:\nbackend/src/app/testing/fakes.py:261:    \"\"\"Mirrors the Workspace port (GitBranchWorkspace) without git: begin/commit/\nbackend/src/app/testing/fakes.py:327:    fail_kind: FailureKind = FailureKind.CONNECTION_ERROR  # retryable by default\nbackend/src/app/testing/fakes.py:384:    \"NoOpWorkspace\",\nbackend/src/infra/runtime/dummy_runner.py:6:with the same shared FailureKind taxonomy as real CLI runners, so dry-run flows\nbackend/src/domain/events/outbox.py:32:    kind: str | None = None  # FailureKind value — rate_limit visibility\nbackend/src/domain/events/outbox.py:39:    kind: str | None = None  # FailureKind value — rate_limit visibility\nbackend/src/infra/runtime/cli_runner.py:6:FailureKind). It knows NOTHING about retries, backoff or ordering — those are\nbackend/src/infra/runtime/factory.py:9:                      FailureKind taxonomy as the real CLI runners