{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"agent_message","text":"The seam is `ExecutionHandler` immediately around `runner.run`: capture an optional main-repository porcelain-status fingerprint after `begin`, compare it immediately after the runner returns (and on `TaskFailed`), then let the existing failure finalization classify it as retryable `TOOL_ERROR`. `GitBranchWorkspace` will provide the capability; `LocalDirWorkspace`, `NoOpWorkspace`, and other fakes remain capability-absent no-ops, with no domain edits."}}
